# Component Rules

## Required file structure
When creating any component, always generate all 4 files together:

```
ComponentName/
├── ComponentName.tsx          # Implementation
├── ComponentName.module.scss  # Scoped SCSS — use brand tokens
├── ComponentName.types.ts     # Props interface/types
└── index.ts                   # re-export default
```

## SCSS pattern
```scss
@use '@/styles/mixins' as m;

.root {
  background: var(--color-bg-surface);
  color: var(--color-text);
  font-family: var(--font-primary);
}

// Variants via data attributes
.button {
  &[data-variant='primary'] { background: var(--gradient-brand); }
  &[data-variant='ghost']   { border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
}
```

## Types pattern
```ts
// ComponentName.types.ts
export type ButtonVariant = 'primary' | 'ghost' | 'glow';

export interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: ButtonVariant;
  children: React.ReactNode;
}
```

## index.ts pattern
```ts
export { default } from './ComponentName';
export type { ComponentNameProps } from './ComponentName.types';
```

## Available mixins (from `src/styles/_mixins.scss`)
- `@include m.gradient-text` — brand gradient text
- `@include m.glow('cyan' | 'blue' | 'purple')` — glow box-shadow
- `@include m.glass` — glassmorphism surface
- `@include m.focus-ring` — accessible focus outline
- `@include m.truncate` — text overflow ellipsis
- `@include m.mobile / tablet / desktop` — breakpoints
